EQUIPMENT MANAGEMENT - /equipment
Access: Admin, Coach

INVENTORY TAB

View inventory - Inventory tab on load - Table of all items showing ID, category, name, source, type, quantity, reorder level, unit cost, and status
Search and filter inventory - Enter search term or select category or type then click Go - GET request to /equipment with query parameters, filtered results returned
Add Inventory Item - Click Add Item, fill modal, click Save Item - POST to /add_inventory_item, inserts item and auto-calculates status as In Stock, Low Stock, or Out of Stock
Status badges - View Status column - Green badge means In Stock, yellow badge means Low Stock, red badge means Out of Stock

ORDERS TAB

View orders - Orders tab - Table of all equipment orders with status badges
Place Order - Click Place Order, select item and supplier and quantity, click Place Order - POST to /create_equipment_order, inserts order with status New Order, flash success shown
View order summary - Bottom left card in Orders tab - Shows counts of New, In Progress, and Received orders
View low stock alerts - Bottom right card in Orders tab - Lists any items not currently In Stock

---

SUPPLIER PORTAL - /supplier
Access: Admin, Supplier

View new orders - New Orders section - Lists all orders with status New Order
Confirm or update a new order - Click Confirm Order and Provide Details, fill modal with status, dates, total cost, vendor notes, click Save Update - POST to /update_supplier_order/order_id, updates order record
Mark order as Received - Set status to Received in update modal and save - Inventory quantity auto-incremented by order quantity, received_to_inventory set to true, item status recalculated
View in-progress and shipped orders - Orders In Progress and Shipped section - Cards for all In Progress and Shipped orders with Update button
View completed orders - Received and Completed Orders table - Shows all Received orders with inventory posted indicator

---

FINANCIAL REPORTING - /finances
Access: Admin, Coach

SUMMARY CARDS

View totals - Page load - Cards show Total Revenue, Total Expenses, Net Balance, Projected Expenses, Projected Revenue, and Projected Net

GAMES TABLE

View game comparisons - Games section - Table with projected versus actual revenue and expenses and variance per game
Click a game row - Click anywhere on a game row - Opens Game Finance Detail modal via async fetch to /game_details/game_id
Add Actual Entry for game - Inside game detail modal click Add Actual Entry - Opens Add Actual Entry modal locked to that game
Add Projection for game - Inside game detail modal click Add Projection - Opens Add Projection modal locked to that game
Save actual entry - Fill form and click Save Entry - POST to /add_financial_entry, inserts into financial_entries linked to game_id
Save projection - Fill form and click Save Projection - POST to /add_financial_projection, inserts into financial_projections linked to game_id
Delete actual entry - Click Delete button in entries table inside modal - POST to /delete_financial_entry/entry_id, removes entry
Delete projection - Click Delete button in projections table inside modal - POST to /delete_financial_projection/projection_id, removes projection
Delete game from modal - Click Delete Game button inside game detail modal - POST to /delete_game/game_id, removes game and all related financial records

PRACTICES TABLE

Click a practice row - Click anywhere on a practice row - Opens Practice Finance Detail modal via async fetch to /practice_details/practice_id
Add Actual Entry or Projection - Same workflow as game modal - POST to /add_financial_entry or /add_financial_projection linked to practice_id
Delete entries or projections - Delete buttons in detail modal - Same delete routes as game entries
Delete practice from modal - Click Delete Practice button - POST to /delete_practice/practice_id, removes practice and related financial records

GENERAL TEAM FINANCES SECTION

View general entries - Bottom table - Shows entries not linked to any game or practice
Click a general entry row - Click a row - Opens General Team Finance Entry modal showing date, type, category, description, and amount
Delete general entry - Click Delete Entry in modal - POST to /delete_financial_entry/entry_id, removes entry and shows flash confirmation
Add General Entry - Click Add General Entry, fill modal, click Save Entry - POST to /add_financial_entry with game_id and practice_id both empty, general entry created

ANNUAL SUMMARY MODAL

Open Annual Summary - Click View Annual Summary button - Opens modal with total revenue, expenses, net cards, and two pie charts
Revenue pie chart - Rendered on modal open - Pie chart showing revenue breakdown by category
Expense pie chart - Rendered on modal open - Pie chart showing expense breakdown by category

